<usermanual>
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	

									FOOD CRAVINGS QUESTIONNAIRE-STATE (FCQ-S)
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	

Script Author: Katja Borchert, Ph.D. (katjab@millisecond.com) for Millisecond Software, LLC
Date: 05-02-2016
last updated:  02-22-2022 by K. Borchert (katjab@millisecond.com) for Millisecond Software, LLC

Script Copyright © 02-22-2022 Millisecond Software

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
BACKGROUND INFO 	
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
This script implements the Food Cravings Questionnaire State (FCQ-S) as described in:

Cepeda-Benito, A., Gleaves, D. H., Williams, T. L., & Erath, S. A. (2000). The
development and validation of the State and Trait food Cravings Questionnaires.
Behavior Therapy, 31, 151-173.

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
OVERVIEW
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
15 5-point Likert questions

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
DURATION 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
the default set-up of the script takes appr. 1.5 minutes to complete

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
DATA FILE INFORMATION 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
The default data stored in the data files are:

(1) Raw data file: 'FCQ_S.iqdat'

date, time:						date and time script was run with the current group/subjectnumber 
subject, group, session:	  	with the current subject/groupnumber/session id
build:							the Inquisit build 

q*_response:					response given (in assigned values)
								Scale: 1 (strongly disagree) - 5 (strongly agree)
								no reversed scored questions
									
q*_latency:						how much time (in ms) the participant spent on the surveypage with this particular 
								question (the last time this particular surveypage was visited)

(2) Summary data file: 'FCQ_S_summary.iqdat' (Inquisit Lab: one data file per participant)

inquisit.version: 						Inquisit version run
computer.platform:					the platform the script was run on (win/mac/ios/android)
startDate:							date script was run
startTime:							time script was started
subjectid:							assigned subject id number
groupid:							assigned group id number
sessionid:							assigned session id number
elapsedTime:						time it took to run script (in ms); measured from onset to offset of script
completed:							0 = script was not completed (prematurely aborted); 
									1 = script was completed (all conditions run)

FCQ_S_Total:		Total Score (Min: 15 - Max: 75)
Desire:				An Intense Desire to Eat (Points: 3-15)
Anticipation:		Anticipation of Positive Reinforcement That May Result From Eating (points: 3 - 15)
Relief:				Anticipation of Relief From Negative States and Feelings as a Result of Eating (points: 3-15)
LackOfControl:		Lack of Control Over Eating	(points: 3 - 15)		
Hunger:				Craving as a Physiological State (i.e., Hunger) (points: 3 - 15)


___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
INSTRUCTIONS 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
see section Editable Parameters
(instructions are not original)

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
EDITABLE CODE 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
check below for (relatively) easily editable parameters, stimuli, instructions etc. 
Keep in mind that you can use this script as a template and therefore always "mess" with the entire code 
to further customize your experiment.

The parameters you can change are:

/pageinstructions:			instructions that appear at the top
/targetFoods:				the target food(s) can be changed here (default: [one or more specific foods])

</usermanual>


*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	EDITABLE PARAMETERS
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************

/pageinstructions:			the instructions that appear at the top of each surveypage

<parameters>
/pageinstructions = "Please indicate how much you agree with each of the following 15 statements RIGHT NOW, at this very moment:
"
/targetFoods = "[one or more specific foods]"
</parameters>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
							REMAINING CODE: Customize after careful consideration only
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	DEFAULTS:
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
requires Inquisit 6.5.2.0

<defaults>
/minimumversion = "6.5.2.0"
/canvasaspectratio = (4,3)
</defaults>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	DATA: this section contains data file information
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************

********************
Summary data
********************

<summarydata>
/columns = (inquisit.version, computer.platform,script.startDate, script.startTime, 
script.subjectId, script.groupId, script.sessionId, script.elapsedTime, 
script.completed, 
expressions.FCQ_S_Total, expressions.Desire, expressions.Anticipation, 
expressions.Relief, expressions.LackOfControl, expressions.Hunger)
</summarydata>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	EXPRESSIONS
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
/Desire:						An Intense Desire to Eat (Points: 3-15)
/Anticipation:					Anticipation of Positive Reinforcement That May Result From Eating (points: 3 - 15)
/Relief:						Anticipation of Relief From Negative States and Feelings as a Result of Eating (points: 3-15)
/LackOfControl:					Lack of Control Over Eating	(points: 3 - 15)		
/Hunger:						Craving as a Physiological State (i.e., Hunger) (points: 3 - 15)
/FCQ_S_Total:					Total Score (Min: 15 - Max: 75)

<expressions>
/Desire = radiobuttons.q1_D.response + radiobuttons.q2_D.response + radiobuttons.q3_D.response 
/Anticipation = radiobuttons.q4_A.response + radiobuttons.q5_A.response + radiobuttons.q6_A.response 
/Relief = radiobuttons.q7_R.response + radiobuttons.q8_R.response + radiobuttons.q9_R.response 
/LackOfControl = radiobuttons.q10_C.response + radiobuttons.q11_C.response + radiobuttons.q12_C.response 
/Hunger = radiobuttons.q13_H.response + radiobuttons.q14_H.response + radiobuttons.q15_H.response 
/FCQ_S_Total = expressions.Desire + expressions.Anticipation + expressions.Relief + expressions.LackOfControl + expressions.Hunger
</expressions>


*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	QUESTIONS
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
Note: by default all questions are required to be answered. To change
/required = false

<radiobuttons q1_D>
/caption = "1. I have an intense desire to eat <%parameters.targetFoods%>."
/ options = ("strongly~ndisagree", "disagree", "neither agree~nnor disagree", "agree", "strongly~nagree")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q2_D>
/caption = "2. I'm craving <%parameters.targetFoods%>."
/ options = ("strongly~ndisagree", "disagree", "neither agree~nnor disagree", "agree", "strongly~nagree")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q3_D>
/caption = "3. I have an urge for <%parameters.targetFoods%>."
/ options = ("strongly~ndisagree", "disagree", "neither agree~nnor disagree", "agree", "strongly~nagree")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q4_A>
/caption = "4. Eating <%parameters.targetFoods%> would make things seem just perfect."
/ options = ("strongly~ndisagree", "disagree", "neither agree~nnor disagree", "agree", "strongly~nagree")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q5_A>
/caption = "5. If I were to eat what I am craving, I am sure my mood would improve."
/ options = ("strongly~ndisagree", "disagree", "neither agree~nnor disagree", "agree", "strongly~nagree")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q6_A>
/caption = "6. Eating <%parameters.targetFoods%> would feel wonderful."
/ options = ("strongly~ndisagree", "disagree", "neither agree~nnor disagree", "agree", "strongly~nagree")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q7_R>
/caption = "7. If I ate something, I wouldn't feel so sluggish and lethargic."
/ options = ("strongly~ndisagree", "disagree", "neither agree~nnor disagree", "agree", "strongly~nagree")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q8_R>
/caption = "8. Satisfying my craving would make me feel less grouchy and irritable."
/ options = ("strongly~ndisagree", "disagree", "neither agree~nnor disagree", "agree", "strongly~nagree")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q9_R>
/caption = "9. I would feel more alert if I could satisfy my craving."
/ options = ("strongly~ndisagree", "disagree", "neither agree~nnor disagree", "agree", "strongly~nagree")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q10_C>
/caption = "10. If I had <%parameters.targetFoods%>, I could not stop eating it."
/ options = ("strongly~ndisagree", "disagree", "neither agree~nnor disagree", "agree", "strongly~nagree")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q11_C>
/caption = "11. My desire to eat <%parameters.targetFoods%> seems overpowering."
/ options = ("strongly~ndisagree", "disagree", "neither agree~nnor disagree", "agree", "strongly~nagree")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q12_C>
/caption = "12. I know I'm going to keep on thinking about <%parameters.targetFoods%> until I actually have it."
/ options = ("strongly~ndisagree", "disagree", "neither agree~nnor disagree", "agree", "strongly~nagree")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q13_H>
/caption = "13. I am hungry."
/ options = ("strongly~ndisagree", "disagree", "neither agree~nnor disagree", "agree", "strongly~nagree")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q14_H>
/caption = "14. If I ate right now, my stomach wouldn't feel as empty."
/ options = ("strongly~ndisagree", "disagree", "neither agree~nnor disagree", "agree", "strongly~nagree")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q15_H>
/caption = "15. I feel weak because of not eating."
/ options = ("strongly~ndisagree", "disagree", "neither agree~nnor disagree", "agree", "strongly~nagree")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	SURVEYPAGES
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************

<surveypage FCQ_S1>
/caption ="<%parameters.pageinstructions%>"
/questions = [1 = q1_D, q2_D, q3_D]
</surveypage>

<surveypage FCQ_S2>
/caption ="<%parameters.pageinstructions%>"
/questions = [1 = q4_A, q5_A, q6_A]
</surveypage>

<surveypage FCQ_S3>
/caption ="<%parameters.pageinstructions%>"
/questions = [1 = q7_R, q8_R, q9_R]
</surveypage>

<surveypage FCQ_S4>
/caption ="<%parameters.pageinstructions%>"
/questions = [1 = q10_C, q11_C, q12_C]
</surveypage>

<surveypage FCQ_S5>
/caption ="<%parameters.pageinstructions%>"
/questions = [1 = q13_H, q14_H, q15_H]
</surveypage>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	SURVEY
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
Notes:
- presents the surveypages
- to take pictures of each screen set /screencapture = true

<survey FCQ_S>
/pages = [
	1 = FCQ_S1; 
	2 = FCQ_S2; 
	3 = FCQ_S3;
	4 = FCQ_S4;
	5 = FCQ_S5;
]
/screencapture = false
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 3%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ subcaptionfontstyle = ("Arial", 1.5%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ itemfontstyle = ("Arial", 3%, true, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ responsefontstyle = ("Arial", 2.5%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ txcolor = (0, 0, 0)
/ showpagenumbers = false
/ showquestionnumbers = false
/showpagenumbers = false
/showquestionnumbers = false
/ navigationbuttonfontstyle = ("Arial", 3%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ navigationbuttonsize = (15%, 5%)
/ backbuttonposition = (20%, 90%)
/ nextbuttonposition = (70%, 90%)
/ finishlabel = "Finish"
</survey>

*******************************************************************************************************************
												End of File
*******************************************************************************************************************